
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `foo2hiperc-wrapper` yek dastoor-e komaki baraye chapgar-haye (printer-ha) rangi va siaah-sefid-e (grayscale) hast ke az protocol-e "foo2zjs" estefade mikonand. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ke chapgar-e khod ra ba estefade az yek rah-andazi-ye (driver) baz (open-source) be rah andazid.  Be zabane sade, in dastoor "wrapper" ast ke kar ra baraye rah andazi chapgar asan mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`   --> ❓ Namayesh rahnama-ye dastoor va gozine-ha.
    🔹 `--version`--> ℹ️ Namayesh version-e `foo2hiperc-wrapper`.
    🔹 `<chapgar>`  --> 🖨️  Esm-e chapgari ke mikhahid az an estefade konid (masalan: HP1020). Agar esm chapgar ra nadehid, dastoor be soorat khodkar chapgar-e pishfarz ra entekhab mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ foo2hiperc-wrapper --help

    🔹  Namayesh rahnama-ye dastoor.

    $ foo2hiperc-wrapper HP1020

    🔹  Rah andazi chapgar-e HP1020 ba rah andazi-ye `foo2zjs`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ foo2hiperc-wrapper

    🔹 Agar chapgar-e pishfarz dar system taeen shode bashad, in dastoor be soorat khodkar an ra ba rah andazi-ye `foo2zjs` rah andazi mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `foo2hiperc-wrapper` command is a helper script for color and grayscale printers that use the "foo2zjs" protocol. It helps you to set up your printer using an open-source driver.  In simple terms, this command is a "wrapper" that makes printer setup easier.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`   --> ❓ Display the command's help and options.
    🔹 `--version`--> ℹ️ Display the `foo2hiperc-wrapper` version.
    🔹 `<printer>` --> 🖨️ The name of the printer you want to use (e.g., HP1020). If you don't provide a printer name, the command will automatically select the default printer.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ foo2hiperc-wrapper --help

    🔹  Displays the command's help information.

    $ foo2hiperc-wrapper HP1020

    🔹  Sets up the HP1020 printer using the `foo2zjs` driver.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ foo2hiperc-wrapper

    🔹 If a default printer is already configured in the system, this command will automatically set it up using the `foo2zjs` driver.
